Kitsap County, Washington, Open File Report 75-7. This map is intended for use by Kitsap County to designate potential landslide hazard areas. Naturally unstable slopes are potential landslide hazard areas. Potential landslide hazard areas present greater-than-normal risk of damage to buildings and injury to people. Therefore, plans for development in mapped unstable areas should include a geotechnical (engineering geology) on-site investigation which is completed prior to County approval of grading and foundation designs.</gco:CharacterString> </gmd:abstract> <gmd:status> <gmd:MD_ProgressCode
